I'm blaming you.

14
00:01:18,458 --> 00:01:20,166
[ASAKURA] Yeah, I think
I'm all right with that.

15
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:24,750
You'll be cuter if you
stay pint-size, anyway.

16
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:26,333
That's not nice.

17
00:01:26,416 --> 00:01:31,166
[KYON]
Hey, Nagato. Are you okay? Here.

18
00:01:34,083 --> 00:01:35,375
Come on.

19
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:39,916
Uh-- Ah!

20
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,708
Th-Thank you, Kyon.

21
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:47,083
[KYON]
Hm?

22
00:01:47,166 --> 00:01:48,958
[ASAKURA] Hm... You know you're
still holding his hand, right?

23
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:50,166
[gasps]

24
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,541
--[NAGATO gasps] Uh, sorry.
--[KYON yelps]

25
00:01:52,625 --> 00:01:55,208
[ASAKURA] Well then, I'll just
be heading out now. Bye!

26
00:01:55,291 --> 00:01:56,291
[NAGATO]
Ah...

27
00:01:56,375 --> 00:01:57,791
But aren't you coming
to the clubroom?

28
00:01:57,875 --> 00:01:59,416
[ASAKURA]
Sorry, I have to miss today.

29
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,458
There are some errands
I need to run.

30
00:02:01,541 --> 00:02:02,916
But don't worry,
I'll still come over

31
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,541
to your place to cook dinner.

32
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:06,333
Great!

33
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:07,500
Oh, and, Kyon?

34
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:08,750
When club activities
are all wrapped up,

35
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,541
maybe you could
walk her home, 'kay?

36
00:02:10,625 --> 00:02:12,833
And you're welcome to stay
for dinner, of course.

37
00:02:12,916 --> 00:02:18,166
I'm off! Market, here
I come! Woo-hoo!

38
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:20,541
Hm. Sale days get her excited.

39
00:02:20,625 --> 00:02:21,625
Uh-huh.

40
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:24,083
Well, off to the
clubroom, huh?

41
00:02:25,541 --> 00:02:26,833
Oh!

42
00:02:52,958 --> 00:02:54,666
[KYON]
Well, it's official.

43
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:56,000
[NAGATO]
What is?

44
00:02:56,083 --> 00:02:57,250
Just that I've been a member
of the Literary Club

45
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,375
for a full week now.

46
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:00,791
So, do I get a
cake or something?

47
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:02,041
You like it so far?

48
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,166
Hm... Well, I'm not really sure

49
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,541
why I joined, honestly.

50
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:08,916
I basically just read
or do my homework, so.

51
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,500
It's pretty much the same stuff
I'd be doing if I wasn't in it.

52
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:13,833
[NAGATO gasps]

53
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,666
[music plays]

54
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:24,833
[NAGATO grunts]

55
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:27,791
--[school bell rings]
--[gasps]

56
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:32,916
[yawns] And thus ends another
productive club meeting.

57
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,416
I guess Literary Clubs aren't
much on variety, are they?

58
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,541
I don't think that's fair.

59
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:39,416
[KYON]
U-Uh--! Sorry!

60
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,791
I'm sure real Literary Clubs
are quite different.

61
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:44,041
Hold on, are you telling
me I joined a fake club?

62
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:49,000
[STUDENTS chattering]

63
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:50,791
[NAGATO]
Maybe this is boring to you.

64
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:54,041
We don't do much in the way of
traditional club activities.

65
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:55,958
But I'd rather read here,
where I can listen

66
00:03:56,041 --> 00:03:57,916
to the noise and laughter
of the other clubs,

67
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,791
than sitting alone
at home with my book.

68
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:04,375
I find it sort of comforting.
That's why I started the club.

69
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:08,000
What I'm getting at is that
you joining wasn't pointless.

70
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,958
[KYON]
Uh--

71
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:15,250
[NAGATO] You're the whole reason
the Literary Club still exists.

72
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,291
I'd be alone without you.

73
00:04:17,375 --> 00:04:19,708
You're an important part
of the club, you know?

74
00:04:19,791 --> 00:04:24,666
So, thank you.
I mean it. I, um...

75
00:04:27,416 --> 00:04:29,500
[gasps]

76
00:04:29,583 --> 00:04:33,041
This last week...
It's been really great!

77
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:37,625
[KYON] Yeah. So, anyway,
we should get going!

78
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:39,250
[NAGATO]
Mm-hm!

79
00:04:46,916 --> 00:04:47,583
[NAGATO gasps]

80
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:48,833
What is it?

81
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:50,625
It's almost Christmas!

82
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,250
Which means we need
to start planning

83
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,708
for the club Christmas party.

84
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:57,375
[KYON] Fake clubs still
have parties? That's cool.

85
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:58,458
[NAGATO]
Can we?

86
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:00,041
You're the one running the show.

87
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:02,000
You are the club
president, right?

88
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:03,583
Yep!

89
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:13,916
[gasps]

90
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,041
Was that someone you know?

91
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,041
Just imagining things.

92
00:05:23,125 --> 00:05:26,125
[NAGATO] This is the story of
a somewhat shy, bookish girl.

93
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:27,833
[KYON]
The light is changing! Let's go!

94
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:29,166
[NAGATO]
Whoops.

95
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:37,500
[NAGATO] Oh! We'll need
a turkey, for sure.

96
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:38,833
[KYON]
Turkey?

97
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:40,833
Oh, are we still talking
about the Christmas party?

98
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:42,208
[NAGATO]
Yeah.

99
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:44,083
You can't have a party
without a turkey, you know?

100
00:05:44,166 --> 00:05:45,208
Oh, is that a thing?

101
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,833
[NAGATO]
Yeah!

102
00:05:50,208 --> 00:05:51,625
[shrieks]

103
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:52,750
[KYON]
Wow...

104
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,458
I didn't think my
hand was that cold.

105
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,583
I'm sorr--

106
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,708
I'm sorry for interrupting

107
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:02,458
this little romantic
comedy moment.

108
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:04,583
So, Asakura, how'd
you do at the sale?

109
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:05,750
A good haul.

110
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:08,750
I may have gone overboard.
My hands hurt.

111
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,125
Will you carry these for me?

112
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:10,958
Hand 'em over.

113
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,875
[ASAKURA]
Thanks!

114
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:14,083
[ASAKURA]
Watch this part carefully.

115
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:14,916
[NAGATO]
What?

116
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,916
Here.

117
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,916
These are heavy!
You did buy a lot!

118
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,083
Ow, ow, ow! So cold and sore.

119
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:22,333
My poor hands.

120
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:25,708
I hate this time
of year, don't you?

121
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:27,416
[KYON gasps]

122
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:30,666
--[KYON] They're like ice cubes!
--There! Much warmer!

123
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:34,000
Now, now, stop thrashing.

124
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:35,333
You don't wanna
break the eggs.

125
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:36,916
[KYON]
You tricked me! I call foul!

126
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,083
[ASAKURA]
Let's review.

127
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:39,416
You see an opening
and you make your move.

128
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,083
Aggressively. Got it?

129
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:46,041
[NAGATO gasps] Incredible!
That's some high-level flirting.

130
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:47,625
Well, are you guys
coming or not?

131
00:06:47,708 --> 00:06:48,833
Yes, Wise Master!

132
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:51,208
[ASAKURA]
Oh, don't call me that.

133
00:06:51,291 --> 00:06:52,583
Hey.

134
00:06:52,666 --> 00:06:59,708
[ASAKURA humming]

135
00:07:02,708 --> 00:07:03,500
[ASAKURA humming]

136
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:05,375
I gotta say, that freaks me out.

137
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:08,166
There's something about the
way you wield that knife...

138
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,208
Hey, Nagato?

139
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:11,333
[NAGATO]
Just a sec. What is it?

140
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:12,750
Well, I heard a rumor.

141
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,625
About a certain club
Christmas party.

142
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,083
Yeah! What do you think?

143
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:17,208
I hate to burst your bubble,

144
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:19,583
but I don't think
it's going to work.

145
00:07:19,666 --> 00:07:20,958
Not in the clubroom, anyway.

146
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,750
The school won't let us.
If you're so set on a party,

147
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,791
why don't we just have
it at home, instead?

148
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:28,958
That way we have
everything we need.

149
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,666
I wanna have it
in the clubroom, okay?

150
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,708
Can we please just
leave it at that?

151
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:34,125
[ASAKURA]
Hm?

152
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,708
[KYON] I admit it: this
looks pretty darn good,

153
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,291
even the vegetables.

154
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:41,666
[ASAKURA giggles] With veggies,
it's all in how you cut them.

155
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,000
[KYON]
Mm!

156
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:49,291
[ASAKURA chuckles]

157
00:07:49,375 --> 00:07:50,416
Have an egg, Nagato.

158
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,916
Go on, I bet you'll like it.

159
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,166
Oh. Thanks.

160
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:56,250
So. Back to the party idea.

161
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:58,375
Why do you wanna hold
it in the clubroom?

162
00:07:58,458 --> 00:07:59,083
[gaggs]

163
00:07:59,166 --> 00:07:59,708
[gasps]

164
00:07:59,791 --> 00:08:00,875
Are you all right?

165
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:03,708
Oh, no! Your cute
sweater got all stained!

166
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:06,333
Come on, hurry!

167
00:08:06,416 --> 00:08:08,666
We need to get it
in the wash quickly.

168
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,875
Um. I can undress myself.

169
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,583
But it's easier without
stuff in my hands.

170
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:15,208
[laughs] You two are
really close, aren't you?

171
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:16,583
[ASAKURA]
This stuff is dangerous.

172
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:18,291
One clumsy move
with a chopstick,

173
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:20,208
and you're covered
in boiling broth.

174
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,083
Nagato is always--

175
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,250
Huh?

176
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:28,791
[screams]

177
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,416
[KYON]
S-Sorry! Sorry!

178
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,250
[ASAKURA shrieks] I forgot
that Kyon was here, too!

179
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:40,541
[KYON]
You think she's okay?

180
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:41,916
Get in there! Go!

181
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,625
[yelps]

182
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:47,416
Hey, how ya doin'?
Is this seat taken?

183
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,791
Okay, great!

184
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:57,291
--[NAGATO] Uh...
--[KYON] I...

185
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,125
--Oh!
--Uh!

186
00:08:58,208 --> 00:08:59,625
No, you first. Go on.

187
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:05,208
Oh! I was just...
I wanted to know...

188
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:06,541
How much did you see?

189
00:09:06,625 --> 00:09:07,916
[KYON]
Strike one!

190
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,875
Some pitchers begin with
a couple of warm-up throws,

191
00:09:09,958 --> 00:09:13,208
but not this one! Nope, it's
straight to the curve ball!

192
00:09:13,291 --> 00:09:15,916
I guess beating around
the bush isn't her style.

193
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:19,250
Well, I saw... Uh... Your belly!

194
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:20,958
Just your waist, I mean!

195
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:22,291
That's really all?

196
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:24,708
Totally! I didn't see
anything else, I promise!

197
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:26,333
[KYON]
Let's see if she bought it.

198
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:27,750
[NAGATO]
Okay. That's good, then.

199
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:29,708
[KYON]
Hook, line, and sinker!

200
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:30,958
[sighs]

201
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:32,833
Um. I do have just one
more question, though.

202
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:33,875
Yeah, shoot.

203
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:36,083
The toughest one's
out of the way.

204
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,916
So you saw my stomach.

205
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,458
What'd you think?

206
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:45,166
[KYON] That question's
a conversational landmine!

207
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,541
And I'm about to get
blown to pieces.

208
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:48,916
[NAGATO]
What's he gonna say?

209
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,208
I think boys like
a little more... meat.

210
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:53,375
[KYON] If I say I liked it,
then I'm the creepy guy

211
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:54,916
who likes her stomach.

212
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,583
But if I say I didn't, then
I'm the jerk who insulted her.

213
00:09:57,666 --> 00:10:00,000
I can't do this on my own!

214
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,666
[KYON]
I can't say that!

215
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,875
Calm down!

216
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:05,958
You're blowing this
way out of proportion.

217
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:07,541
It's not like you're a bad guy.

218
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:08,791
You've got nothing to hide.

219
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:12,458
Just tell her the truth,
and it'll be fine.

220
00:10:12,541 --> 00:10:14,041
[KYON]
Your stomach's nice.

221
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:16,083
I-I mean, I don't think there's
anything wrong with it.

222
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:18,041
It's not like I have
a stomach fetish.

223
00:10:18,125 --> 00:10:20,541
[NAGATO]
Hm? Stomach fetish? What's that?

224
00:10:20,625 --> 00:10:22,500
[KYON]
Mm...

225
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,416
Nothing! I'm an idiot
who talks too much.

226
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:27,250
Forget I said anything,
okay? I'm begging you!

227
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:30,125
Uh. Yeah. Sure.

228
00:10:30,208 --> 00:10:32,291
[KYON sighs]
There's gotta be something else

229
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:35,833
we can talk about.
New subject. New subject.

230
00:10:38,583 --> 00:10:40,833
So, why's it so important
that we have the party

231
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,583
in the actual clubroom?

232
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:44,125
Wouldn't it make more
sense to have it here,

233
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,583
like Asakura said?

234
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:46,958
[gasps]

235
00:10:47,041 --> 00:10:48,416
[NAGATO]
It wouldn't be the same.

236
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,625
The party isn't really
about Christmas.

237
00:10:50,708 --> 00:10:53,000
It's about celebrating
the club itself.

238
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:54,000
With a party?

239
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:55,541
Yeah. That's right.

240
00:10:55,625 --> 00:10:58,125
To celebrate the fact
that there is a club.

241
00:10:58,208 --> 00:10:59,458
That you guys joined.

242
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:01,458
That we're all
doing this together.

243
00:11:01,541 --> 00:11:03,375
[ASAKURA] And you think the
best place to have a party

244
00:11:03,458 --> 00:11:05,625
for the club is in
the clubroom, huh?

245
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:06,791
That's right.

246
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,750
Having it there would
mean a lot to me.

247
00:11:11,875 --> 00:11:14,291
If that's the case,
I guess it can't be helped.

248
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:16,333
Okay, then. Let's do it!

249
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:17,708
Really?

250
